    </p>
  </header>

  <section class="definition-entries" aria-label="Definitions">
    <div class="definition-card-stack">
      <ul role="list">
        <li role="listitem">
          <span class="definition-emoji" aria-hidden="true">&#x1F4E3;</span>
          <p>
            "to arc up" (Australian slang) - to rise loudly in defense of people and planet. To take action when it matters
            most.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li role="listitem">
          <span class="definition-emoji" aria-hidden="true">&#x1F9EC;</span>
          <p>
            Investigating plasma-activated water as a tool for soil regeneration, ecological restoration, and bridging
            physics with biology for planetary repair.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li role="listitem">
          <span class="definition-emoji" aria-hidden="true">&#x1F30D;</span>
          <p>
            An open invitation to students, scientists, engineers, tinkerers, and technologists ready to collaborate on
            technology that serves life and creates a better future for all.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li role="listitem">
          <span class="definition-emoji" aria-hidden="true">&#x1F91D;</span>
          <p>
            Built on principles, dignity, ethics, and the belief that knowledge belongs in the commons&mdash;not locked behind
            patents.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="definition-intro" aria-label="Personal introduction">
    <p>
      I'm Ali. Arc^ started as my response to a question: if I make the same choices as the good people before me, what world
      would it create? Right now, arc^ is just one person, and it's a framework that refuses the old processes of innovation.
      My hope? arc^ will flourish into a global community of future conscious development, changemakers, and pioneers.
    </p>
  </section>

  <nav class="definition-cta-group" aria-label="Definition page navigation">
    <a class="button" href={withBase("/why")}>Why arc^?</a>
    <a class="button button-outline" href={withBase("/projects")}>Explore projects</a>
  </nav>
</main>

